---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | FNE"
  description="Privacy policy for the Figma Naming Enforcer (FNE) CLI tool and Figma plugin."
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main-content">
    <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl font-bold text-primary-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-primary-500">Effective Date: March 26, 2026</p>
        <div class="prose prose-primary mt-8 max-w-none">
          <p>Halisonworks AS ("we," "us," "our") develops the Figma Naming Enforcer (FNE). This Privacy Policy explains data handling.</p>

          <h2>Data Controller</h2>
          <p>Halisonworks AS, Norway. Contact: privacy@halisonworks.com</p>

          <h2>CLI Tool</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>The CLI reads your Figma file via the Figma REST API or MCP using your personal access token.</li>
            <li>Layer names and structure are sent to the Anthropic API (Claude) for analysis.</li>
            <li>The generated rename manifest is saved locally on your machine.</li>
            <li>Halisonworks does not receive, store, or have access to your Figma data or API tokens.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Figma Plugin</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>The plugin runs within the Figma environment.</li>
            <li>It reads and modifies layer names only based on manifests you import.</li>
            <li>No data is sent to Halisonworks servers.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Marketing Website</h2>
          <p>Analytics: pages visited, session duration (PostHog).</p>

          <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Data Shared</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Figma API</td><td>Read Figma file structure</td><td>Layer names, structure (via your token)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Anthropic (Claude)</td><td>LLM analysis for naming suggestions</td><td>Layer names, naming standard (via your API key)</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p>Your API keys are stored locally in environment variables or config files. They are never transmitted to Halisonworks.</p>

          <h2>Your Rights</h2>
          <p>CLI and plugin data stays on your machine and in your Figma environment. For website data, contact privacy@halisonworks.com.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
